'''Aérocentre''' is a [[France|French]] [[Business cluster|cluster]] of [[aerospace engineering]] companies and research centres created in 2009.<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.lanouvellerepublique.fr/Indre/Actualite/Economie-social/n/Contenus/Articles/2015/10/26/Aerocentre-structure-la-filiere-aeronautique-2512484 Aérocentre structure la filière aéronautique]</ref><ref>{{fr}}[http://www.aerobuzz.fr/aviation-generale/breve/le-pole-aerocentre-soutien-le-bia Le Pôle Aérocentre soutien le BIA de l’aéro-club de Sologne]</ref> It is in the [[Regions of France|region]] of [[Centre-Val de Loire]] in the middle of [[France]].<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.larep.fr/france-monde/actualites/economie-politique/eco-finances/2013/10/05/aerocentre-veut-se-rapprocher-dautres-regions-de-france_1716830.html Aérocentre veut se rapprocher d’autres régions de France]</ref>
==Overview== There are over 321 companies. About 20,000 people work there in the aviation and space flight [[industry|industries]].
The headquarters of Aérocentre is located at the [[Châteauroux-Centre "Marcel Dassault" Airport]]. The chairman of the cluster is Jean-Michel SANCHEZ.
