'''Carpisa''' is an Italian manufacturer and retailer of luggage, handbags, wallets and accessories, with over 600 outlets worldwide.

Carpisa was founded in 2001, is owned by [[Kuvera SpA]], and has a "franchise network of more than 600 stores in Italy and abroad".<ref name="carpisa.it">{{cite web|url=http://www.carpisa.it/en/company.html|title=Carpisa - Italian-designed suitcases since 2001|publisher=}}</ref> Carpisa has been called a "[[fast fashion]] brand".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.italy24.ilsole24ore.com/art/business-and-economy/2015-08-25/fast-fashion-brands-yamamay-and-carpisa-have-teamed-up-and-are-now-taking-on-the-german-market-103057.php?uuid=ACtUaRm|title=Italian fast fashion brands Yamamay and Carpisa  take on the German market|publisher=}}</ref>

The headquarters building of over 10,000 square meters, the CasaCarpisa, is located in the [[Nola Interporto]], in [[Nola]], Italy.<ref name="carpisa.it"/>

